00:24:54,009 --> 00:24:57,323
was very different than anything
he'd done before.

530
00:24:57,357 --> 00:24:59,601
What do you think he found here
that was good for him?

531
00:24:59,636 --> 00:25:02,604
Well, he lived a pretty
low-profile life in Berlin.

532
00:25:02,639 --> 00:25:05,883
I have to say that.

533
00:25:05,918 --> 00:25:07,298
He could be anonymous here.

534
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:10,647
Like, everybody admired him,
but nobody talked to him.

535
00:25:10,681 --> 00:25:14,271
That's a big advantage.

536
00:25:14,305 --> 00:25:15,928
And a funny thing is

537
00:25:15,962 --> 00:25:20,829
when you have that sort of
visionary pregnancy

538
00:25:20,864 --> 00:25:22,762
that you say
something's gonna come,

539
00:25:22,797 --> 00:25:26,594
something's gonna
fall from the sky,

540
00:25:26,628 --> 00:25:28,872
it does.

541
00:25:31,875 --> 00:25:34,636
Now, back in the early '70s
when David Bowie arrived,

542
00:25:34,671 --> 00:25:36,804
a lot of people don't realize,
but Berlin was surrounded.

543
00:25:36,811 --> 00:25:39,779
I mean, it was
essentially an island

544
00:25:39,814 --> 00:25:40,853
during much of that period.

545
00:25:40,884 --> 00:25:42,782
Yes, yeah.

546
00:25:42,817 --> 00:25:45,233
Outside of
whatever Bowie was doing,

547
00:25:45,267 --> 00:25:46,717
what was... what was it like

548
00:25:46,752 --> 00:25:49,030
in West Berlin at that time?

549
00:25:49,064 --> 00:25:51,929
It was like pressure cooking.

550
00:25:51,964 --> 00:25:56,209
You know, it was like
pressure cooking.

551
00:25:56,244 --> 00:25:58,764
West Berlin was
surrounded by the Wall

552
00:25:58,798 --> 00:26:01,629
and there were just three
roads leading to West Berlin

553
00:26:01,663 --> 00:26:04,977
and they were controlled by
the Russians, basically.

554
00:26:05,011 --> 00:26:09,809
So why would a walled city

555
00:26:09,844 --> 00:26:12,329
surrounded by hostile forces

556
00:26:12,363 --> 00:26:16,333
be such a hothouse
for art, music,

557
00:26:16,367 --> 00:26:18,093
and free expression?

558
00:26:18,128 --> 00:26:20,924
West Berlin was always
very international.

559
00:26:20,958 --> 00:26:23,616
We had, like,
people were flying in

560
00:26:23,651 --> 00:26:24,997
from all walks of life.

561
00:26:25,031 --> 00:26:27,620
Artists from all genres
were here,

562
00:26:27,655 --> 00:26:31,244
and we were surrounded by East.

563
00:26:31,279 --> 00:26:34,938
The Wall was a solid resistance,

564
00:26:34,972 --> 00:26:37,423
and you need a strong enemy to
build a strong muscle.

565
00:26:37,457 --> 00:26:39,805
And people who were living here

566
00:26:39,839 --> 00:26:42,014
had to improvise a lot.

567
00:26:43,187 --> 00:26:46,639
It's what is seen by many as,

568
00:26:46,674 --> 00:26:48,676
you know, a golden period.

569
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:50,332
The Weimar Era was in fact

570
00:26:50,367 --> 00:26:54,371
a hotbed for music
and culture and art

571
00:26:54,405 --> 00:26:56,718
in between two
really awful events...

572
00:26:56,753 --> 00:26:58,030
Yes.

573
00:26:58,064 --> 00:26:59,058
Followed by the wartime years,

574
00:26:59,065 --> 00:27:00,377
followed by,

575
00:27:00,411 --> 00:27:03,829
postwar
the village was in ruins.

576
00:27:05,416 --> 00:27:07,695
When were the good times?

577
00:27:07,729 --> 00:27:10,214
I have a...

578
00:27:10,249 --> 00:27:15,012
I have a very complex
answer to that,

579
00:27:15,047 --> 00:27:17,394
and that is,
the best times are now.

580
00:27:17,428 --> 00:27:21,294
We have all the freedoms
that we want, you know.

581
00:27:21,329 --> 00:27:23,814
I think the best times are now.

582
00:27:26,852 --> 00:27:28,405
♪

