704
00:33:17,409 --> 00:33:19,825
The ubiquitous and deeply loved

705
00:33:19,859 --> 00:33:22,103
signature street foods of Berlin

706
00:33:22,138 --> 00:33:25,072
are currywurst and doner.

707
00:33:25,106 --> 00:33:27,384
And what better place to enjoy
such delicious treats

708
00:33:27,419 --> 00:33:30,491
than in front of a classic
of German cinema.

709
00:33:30,525 --> 00:33:33,528
In this case, Fritz Lang's
silent masterpiece,

710
00:33:33,563 --> 00:33:36,083
"Metropolis,"
an artifact of the Weimar Era

711
00:33:36,117 --> 00:33:38,154
that's still
politically relevant.

712
00:33:38,188 --> 00:33:40,156
It's seen as a cornerstone
of cinema

713
00:33:40,190 --> 00:33:42,503
and the mother of sci-fi movies.

714
00:33:42,537 --> 00:33:45,333
Billy Wagner has invited me
to a midnight showing

715
00:33:45,368 --> 00:33:48,578
at the booze- and food-friendly
Lichtblick-Kino movie house

716
00:33:48,612 --> 00:33:50,787
in Prenzlauer Berg.

717
00:33:50,821 --> 00:33:54,204
♪

718
00:33:54,239 --> 00:33:55,267
He's the co-owner and sommelier

719
00:33:55,274 --> 00:33:58,346
at the Michelin-starred
restaurant

720
00:33:58,381 --> 00:34:01,177
Nobelhart & Schmutzig
in Kreuzberg.

721
00:34:01,211 --> 00:34:04,214
The question of the day being,
what German wines

722
00:34:04,249 --> 00:34:07,355
pair best with a utilitarian
treat like currywurst?

723
00:34:07,390 --> 00:34:10,082
Fried pork sausage
smothered in ketchup

724
00:34:10,117 --> 00:34:14,224
and a dusting of curry powder.

725
00:34:14,259 --> 00:34:16,882
Now, how did this become
a beloved dish?

726
00:34:16,916 --> 00:34:18,194
I have no idea.

727
00:34:18,228 --> 00:34:20,713
A lot of flavor, it's spicy,

728
00:34:20,748 --> 00:34:22,405
it's fat, it's salt.

729
00:34:22,439 --> 00:34:25,166
It's roasted, then you have
fries with it.

730
00:34:25,201 --> 00:34:26,305
- Mm-hmm.
- It's...

731
00:34:26,340 --> 00:34:28,273
Oh, I understand why
people eat it.

732
00:34:28,307 --> 00:34:29,308
Alcohol.

733
00:34:29,343 --> 00:34:31,138
Drunk food, yeah, well, yes.

734
00:34:32,518 --> 00:34:34,486
But at the end, it's
a very cheap thing, you know.

735
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:37,661
You get two sausage with fries

736
00:34:37,696 --> 00:34:41,251
with a beer,
when you pay much, 10 Euro.

737
00:34:41,286 --> 00:34:43,150
Oh, so like a quick
worker's lunch.

738
00:34:43,184 --> 00:34:45,255
Yes, yeah.

739
00:34:45,290 --> 00:34:47,223
So what wine would you
suggest with this?

740
00:34:47,257 --> 00:34:49,915
We should try
[indistinct] champagne.

