I mean, I don't know how
they make it or extend it

788
00:36:42,821 --> 00:36:44,512
or whatever the hell it is.

789
00:36:44,547 --> 00:36:46,963
I don't really care
what's in it.

790
00:36:46,997 --> 00:36:48,378
It's meat.

791
00:36:48,413 --> 00:36:51,692
I don't want grass-fed

792
00:36:51,726 --> 00:36:53,728
Colorado or Australian lamb

793
00:36:53,763 --> 00:36:55,765
on my... on my doner kebab.

794
00:36:55,799 --> 00:36:57,698
I want... I want a... I want this.

795
00:36:57,732 --> 00:37:00,287
You know, especially again,
if I'm a drunk late at night

796
00:37:00,321 --> 00:37:02,634
watching "Metropolis"...

797
00:37:04,463 --> 00:37:08,295
♪

798
00:37:18,097 --> 00:37:20,962
Berlin has a dark side

799
00:37:20,997 --> 00:37:23,068
but you knew this.

800
00:37:23,102 --> 00:37:25,933
You don't have to look too hard.

801
00:37:25,967 --> 00:37:28,798
But renowned photographer,
Miron Zownir,

802
00:37:28,832 --> 00:37:32,353
has been looking with a fixed
gaze on people in the margins

803
00:37:32,388 --> 00:37:34,010
for decades.

804
00:37:37,047 --> 00:37:40,361
♪

805
00:37:40,396 --> 00:37:42,743
For over 40 years,
he's worked diligently

806
00:37:42,777 --> 00:37:45,090
to capture the world's
darker shades,

807
00:37:45,124 --> 00:37:47,748
its most marginalized people,

808
00:37:47,782 --> 00:37:50,406
the outsiders,
the transgressive,

809
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:53,478
the forgotten,
the desperate and depraved,

810
00:37:53,512 --> 00:37:58,862
always in a nonjudgmental,
unblinking way.

811
00:37:58,897 --> 00:38:01,934
These are some of the shots
we can put on TV.

812
00:38:01,969 --> 00:38:04,316
Many we can't.

813
00:38:04,351 --> 00:38:06,594
I urge you

814
00:38:06,629 --> 00:38:09,321
to find them.

815
00:38:11,496 --> 00:38:13,636
You've shot a lot of hustlers,

816
00:38:13,670 --> 00:38:15,603
dope addicts,

817
00:38:15,638 --> 00:38:18,986
prostitutes.

818
00:38:19,020 --> 00:38:21,954
How did you approach
your subjects?

819
00:38:21,989 --> 00:38:23,473
Right up, right in, picture,

820
00:38:23,508 --> 00:38:24,812
or do you establish
a relationship?

821
00:38:24,819 --> 00:38:28,444
Well, it always depended
on the situation.

822
00:38:28,478 --> 00:38:31,619
Some were not aware of me,

823
00:38:31,654 --> 00:38:33,621
others were exhibitionists.

824
00:38:33,656 --> 00:38:37,004
I had fights,
but most of the time

825
00:38:37,038 --> 00:38:38,626
I didn't have any problems

826
00:38:38,661 --> 00:38:41,077
because they were
situations I knew,

827
00:38:41,111 --> 00:38:43,355
okay, now I better retreat

828
00:38:43,390 --> 00:38:44,805
or I get my ass kicked.

829
00:38:44,839 --> 00:38:49,396
I had a very good sense of
how far you can go.

830
00:38:49,430 --> 00:38:49,930
♪

831
00:38:55,194 --> 00:38:58,508
In recent years, Miron has
been making films as well.

832
00:38:58,543 --> 00:39:02,512
Shooting in abandoned spaces,
celebrating all that is taboo,

833
00:39:02,547 --> 00:39:03,893
all that is wrong...

834
00:39:03,927 --> 00:39:07,483
All that is right
about Berlin...

835
00:39:09,761 --> 00:39:12,695
With an unflinching gaze
and a genuine affection

836
00:39:12,729 --> 00:39:16,664
for his subjects and characters.

837
00:39:16,699 --> 00:39:20,496
♪

838
00:39:22,014 --> 00:39:24,016
Berlin has a reputation
as a place that you can come

839
00:39:24,051 --> 00:39:27,192
and be anything you want,
behave pretty much as you want.

840
00:39:27,226 --> 00:39:28,469
Nobody's gonna hassle with you.

841
00:39:28,504 --> 00:39:29,332
Mm-hmm.

842
00:39:29,367 --> 00:39:32,956
Is that true,
do you think, and why?

843
00:39:32,991 --> 00:39:35,476
Endemic art is still possible.

844
00:39:35,511 --> 00:39:36,615
This is really important.

845
00:39:36,650 --> 00:39:40,550
You can create here
independently,

846
00:39:40,585 --> 00:39:41,896
affording your little space...

847
00:39:41,931 --> 00:39:43,484
Mm-hmm.

848
00:39:43,519 --> 00:39:45,417
And do what the [...]
you want to do.

849
00:39:45,452 --> 00:39:46,970
Of all the capitals in Europe,

850
00:39:47,005 --> 00:39:49,939
it's still the cheapest
and more affordable.

851
00:39:49,973 --> 00:39:51,699
Maybe you don't get anywhere

852
00:39:51,734 --> 00:39:53,218
and maybe
you don't make much money,

853
00:39:53,252 --> 00:39:55,082
but you can create freely.

854
00:39:55,116 --> 00:39:56,566
- Right.
- No artist

855
00:39:56,601 --> 00:39:58,637
in New York City,
Paris, or London

856
00:39:58,672 --> 00:39:59,880
can do this anymore.

857
00:39:59,914 --> 00:40:01,709
Well, you said,
you can't even rent a space.

858
00:40:01,744 --> 00:40:03,815
- No. Yeah, yeah.
- It's impossible.

859
00:40:03,849 --> 00:40:07,577
You can't... only if you're
really established artist,

860
00:40:07,612 --> 00:40:09,234
you can live in these places.

861
00:40:09,268 --> 00:40:11,754
So you can come to Berlin
and you can have maybe

862
00:40:11,788 --> 00:40:15,551
a little show in
some basement or cellar,

863
00:40:15,585 --> 00:40:18,968
and at least it's a start
and it's an interaction,

864
00:40:19,002 --> 00:40:21,626
and this is good and this is
really good about Berlin,

865
00:40:21,660 --> 00:40:23,593
it was always good about Berlin.

866
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:27,200
♪

867
00:40:38,539 --> 00:40:39,039
♪

868
00:40:48,169 --> 00:40:50,171
Echoes of lives lived,

869
00:40:50,206 --> 00:40:52,139
lives lost.

870
00:40:52,173 --> 00:40:56,108
No other city has
been repeatedly so powerful

871
00:40:56,143 --> 00:40:59,629
then fallen so low.

872
00:40:59,664 --> 00:41:02,287
Few other cities
have been so shaped

873
00:41:02,321 --> 00:41:04,185
by individual imaginations

874
00:41:04,220 --> 00:41:06,636
either brilliantly creative

875
00:41:06,671 --> 00:41:08,569
or unspeakably evil.

876
00:41:08,604 --> 00:41:11,192
Start again, start again.

877
00:41:11,227 --> 00:41:13,022
Look back at the past.

878
00:41:13,056 --> 00:41:14,506
Never forget it.

879
00:41:14,541 --> 00:41:16,163
Like an Irish playwright said,

880
00:41:16,197 --> 00:41:20,132
"You must go on.
I can't go on.

881
00:41:20,167 --> 00:41:21,789
I'll go on."

882
00:41:21,824 --> 00:41:25,310
♪

883
00:41:28,727 --> 00:41:29,227
♪

884
00:41:46,193 --> 00:41:47,056
♪

